description.narrative: To ensure that children with disabilities receive quality education, the capacities in the education sector to use assistive technologies for teaching were strengthened. The social and emotional skills program was expanded to 1/3 of all primary and secondary schools, covering now over 20,000 students. Preparations for a comprehensive education sector review to carried out in 2020 were undertaken. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:16/12/2019
